# Styling System Guidelines

## Core Styling Architecture

The styling system is built on Tailwind CSS v4 with a comprehensive theme system defined in [src/styles.css](mdc:src/styles.css).

## CSS Structure

### Theme Definition
- **CSS Custom Properties**: Defined in `:root` and `.dark` selectors
- **Color System**: Uses OKLCH color space for better color management
- **Radius System**: Configurable border radius scale (xs, sm, md, lg, xl)
- **Typography**: Geist Sans and Geist Mono font families

### Layer Organization
```css
@layer base {
  /* Global base styles and reusable page containers */
}

@layer utilities {
  /* Custom utility classes for specific patterns */
}
```

## Reusable CSS Classes

### Page Layout Classes (defined in [src/styles.css](mdc:src/styles.css))
- `.page-container`: Main page wrapper with responsive padding
- `.content-container`: Content grid with consistent spacing
- `.list-container`: List wrapper with item spacing
- `.section-container`: Section wrapper for grouped content
- `.title-container`: Title/heading container with proper spacing
- `.meta-container`: Metadata container with tight spacing
- `.hide-on-mobile`: Responsive utility to hide on mobile

### Utility Classes
- `.bullet-list`: Styled list with custom bullets
- `.bullet-item`: Individual list item with bullet styling
- `.bullet-dot`: Custom bullet dot styling
- `.bullet-text`: Text styling for bullet items

## Theme Integration

### Color System
All colors use CSS custom properties that automatically switch between light/dark modes:
- Primary colors: `--primary`, `--primary-foreground`
- Secondary colors: `--secondary`, `--secondary-foreground`
- Accent colors: `--accent`, `--accent-foreground`
- Semantic colors: `--destructive`, `--muted`, `--border`, etc.
- Chart colors: `--chart-1` through `--chart-5`
- Sidebar colors: Complete sidebar color system

### Consumer Requirements
Projects using passport-ui must:
1. Install `@tailwindcss/postcss` and `tailwindcss` v4
2. Configure postcss.config with `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin
3. Import `passport-ui/styles.css` in their main CSS file
4. Ensure Tailwind processes the passport-ui styles